---
import PhoneFrame from './PhoneFrame.astro';
---

<section class="py-24 sm:py-32 px-5 sm:px-8 section-divide">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold sm:text-center mb-4 tracking-[-0.02em] reveal">
      How it works
    </h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary sm:text-center text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-xl sm:mx-auto mb-12 reveal stagger-1">
      A lightweight Rust agent runs on each of your machines and safely opens phone access to your tmux sessions. Connect over LAN or Tailscale, authenticated with a token. Read output, send input, browse files. All self-hosted, nothing leaves your network.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 reveal stagger-2">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-bg-card border border-border hover:border-border-light transition-colors">
        <div class="text-primary font-mono text-xs mb-3 tracking-wider">01</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Install the agent, get the app</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg leading-relaxed">Install the Rust binary on your machines. Download Marmy on your iPhone. Pair with a token from <code class="text-text-primary">marmy-agent pair</code>. You are up and running.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-bg-card border border-border hover:border-border-light transition-colors">
        <div class="text-primary font-mono text-xs mb-3 tracking-wider">02</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Or let Claude Code do it</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg leading-relaxed">Everything is open source. Point Claude Code at the repo and it will build and configure both the agent and the app for your OS. No App Store required.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-text-secondary sm:text-center text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-xl sm:mx-auto mt-10 reveal stagger-3">
      This isn't read-only monitoring. Spin up new sessions, browse any file on your machines, and kick off work from your phone. Full control, not just a window into what's already running.
    </p>

    <!-- Machines screenshot -->
    <div class="flex justify-center mt-12 reveal stagger-4">
      <PhoneFrame
        src="/screenshots/landing.png"
        alt="Marmy Machines screen showing MacBook Pro, Rpi5, Mac Mini, RpiZero, and EC2"
        class="w-[270px] sm:w-[300px]"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
